âš ï¸ O make-aggrid requer Python 3.10 ou superior por depender do streamlit-aggrid =1.1.2.

### Uso BÃ¡sico
```python
import pandas as pd
import streamlit as st
from st_aggrid import AgGrid
from make_aggrid import make_grid

df = pd.read_csv("dados.csv")

grid_options = make_grid(df)

grid_response = AgGrid(
    st.session_state.df,
    gridOptions=grid_options,
    enable_enterprise_modules=False,
    fit_columns_on_grid_load=True,
    allow_unsafe_jscode=True,
    height=400
)
```

## ðŸŽ¯ Recursos incluÃ­dos

- Filtros automÃ¡ticos para texto, nÃºmero e datas
- FormataÃ§Ã£o brasileira para nÃºmeros e datas (`pt-BR`)
- Alinhamento de colunas conforme tipo
- EdiÃ§Ã£o inline
- PaginaÃ§Ã£o e animaÃ§Ãµes

### ðŸ§ª Exemplo AvanÃ§ado com Streamlit

```python
import streamlit as st
import pandas as pd
from st_aggrid import AgGrid
from make_aggrid import make_grid

data = {
    "Nome": ["Ana", "JoÃ£o", "Carlos"],
    "Idade": [23, 35, 29],
    "SalÃ¡rio": [3000.50, 5000.00, 4200.75],
    "Data de AdmissÃ£o": pd.to_datetime(["2020-01-15", "2019-03-10", "2021-07-22"])
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

st.title("Tabela Interativa com AgGrid")

grid_options = make_grid(df)
AgGrid(df, gridOptions=grid_options, editable=True, fit_columns_on_grid_load=True)
```

